    <h2>About the Exam</h2>
    <p>The SSC GD Constable exam is conducted each year by the Staff Selection Commission to recruit General Duty Constables in CAPFs (like BSF, CRPF, SSB, CISF, ITBP), Assam Rifles, and SSF.</p>

    <h2>Who Can Apply?</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Education: Class 10 pass</li>
      <li>Age: 18‚Äì23 years (relaxation for SC/ST/OBC/Sports as per norms) :contentReference[oaicite:0]{index=0}</li>
      <li>Nationality: Indian</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Job Roles</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>GD Constable: Security roles, patrolling, administrative duties in CAPFs and Assam Rifles</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Exam Pattern</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Stage 1 ‚Äì CBT:</strong> 80 MCQs for 160 marks in 60 mins (Reasoning, GK, Maths, English/Hindi). Negative marking: 0.25 per wrong answer. :contentReference[oaicite:1]{index=1}</li>
      <li><strong>Stage 2 ‚Äì Physical Tests (PET & PST):</strong>  
        ‚Ä¢ PET: Men‚Äî5 km in 24 min; Women‚Äî1.6 km in 8.5 min (Ladakh region has special timings) :contentReference[oaicite:2]{index=2}  
        ‚Ä¢ PST (Physical Standard): Height & chest criteria vary by category (e.g., 170 cm for General male; 162.5 cm for ST NE region) :contentReference[oaicite:3]{index=3}
      </li>
    </ul>

